comments.body:
@pierreozoux I've created https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/1930 which I think will address the majority of your concerns.  If you think I can add further to that to help with your concerns, please let me know.

'All I wanted to do is build a Dockerfile, rootless on my mac, or on a classic kubernetes cluster, without configuring anything. I really though that buildah was for this. Maybe I didn't understand?'

That was definitely a bit of a hole in our tutorial that I hope my recent changes clarified.  You can't run Buildah (or Podman) in as a 'rootless user' out of the box.  The administrator of the system has to do a little bit of configuration beforehand.  I've added a section to the tutorial with a pointer to the page that lists that necessary configuration for a rootless user.  I did not yet put together a "Quick Start" page, but I think that's a good thought and I'm letting that bubble in my brain for a bit and hope to create one soon.
